'''公共诚信中心'''（{{lang-en|'''Center for Public Integrity'''}}，缩写作{{lang|en|'''CPI'''}}）是一个位于美国的非盈利新闻调查组织，其初衷是「揭示有权力的公众以及私人机构的滥权、腐败和玩忽职守等行为，以迫使他们诚实、正直、负责地行使权力，并且以公众利益为先」<ref name="about">{{cite web |url=http://www.iwatchnews.org/about |title=About The Center for Public Integrity |accessdate=2012-06-09 |work=Center for Public Integrity |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120603161449/http://www.iwatchnews.org/about |archivedate=2012-06-03 }}</ref>。其初始成员只有50人，但CPI現在是美国最大的无党派非盈利的调查中心之一<ref name="huff">{{cite web |url=http://www.poynter.org/latest-news/mediawire/155573/cpi-reduces-staff-to-compensate-for-2-million-budget-hole/ |title=PI reduces staff to compensate for $2 million budget hole |accessdate=2012-06-09 |date=December 9, 2011 |publisher=Poynter Institute |archive-date=2013-06-18 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6HSJhptwY?url=http://www.poynter.org/latest-news/mediawire/155573/cpi-reduces-staff-to-compensate-for-2-million-budget-hole/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。它赢得了2014年的[[普利策奖|普利策奖]]——普利策调查性报道奖<ref name="Pulitzer.org">{{cite web |url=http://www.pulitzer.org/citation/2014-Investigative-Reporting |title=The 2014 Pulitzer Prize Winners Investigative Reporting |accessdate=2014-07-29 |work=[[普立茲獎|Pulitzer.org]] |archive-date=2016-01-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160115113338/http://www.pulitzer.org/citation/2014-Investigative-Reporting |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

CPI以独立<ref name="NYT_2006">{{cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2006/06/21/opinion/21Wed3.html |title=Razzle-Dazzle 'Em Ethics Reform |accessdate=27 November 2015 |date=26 June 2016 |publisher=New York Times |archive-date=2020-11-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201121061550/https://www.nytimes.com/2006/06/21/opinion/21Wed3.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="AP_1996_">{{cite news |title = Buchanan Campaign Chief Has Milita Ties |last=Galvin |first=Kevin |date=1996 |agency=Associated Press }}</ref>、无党派<ref name="NYT_2012">{{Cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/20/opinion/the-states-get-a-poor-report-card.html |title=The States Get a Poor Report Card |accessdate=27 November 2015 |date=19 March 2012 |publisher=New York Times |archive-date=2020-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111171048/http://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/20/opinion/the-states-get-a-poor-report-card.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.philly.com/1996-02-16/news/25655765_1_larry-pratt-insider-advisers-outsider |title=`Outsider' Runs Filled With `Insider' Advisers |last=Goldstein |first=Steve |date=1996-02-16 |newspaper=Philadelphia Inquirer |accessdate=19 June 2013 |archive-date=2016-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303193813/http://articles.philly.com/1996-02-16/news/25655765_1_larry-pratt-insider-advisers-outsider |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="FAQ">{{cite web |url=http://www.iwatchnews.org/about/our-organization/frequently-asked-questions |title=Frequently Asked Questions |accessdate=2012-06-09 |work=Center for Public Integrity |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120615050642/http://www.iwatchnews.org/about/our-organization/frequently-asked-questions |archivedate=2012-06-15 }}</ref>以及进步<ref name="fair.org">{{cite web |url=http://www.fair.org/index.php?page=1149 |title=Spectrum Narrows Further in 2002: Progressive, domestic think tanks see drop |accessdate=2012-06-09 |date=July–August 2003 |work=Fairness and Accuracy in Reporting |archive-date=2012-10-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121027053217/http://www.fair.org/index.php?page=1149 |dead-url=no }}</ref>著称的第三方监管组织<ref name="NYT_2012"/><ref name="NYT_2015">{{cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/politics/first-draft/2015/09/10/bernie-sanders-has-a-fan-in-the-james-bond-actor-daniel-craig/ |title=Bernie Sanders Has a Fan in the James Bond Actor Daniel Craig |accessdate=27 November 2015 |author=Rappeport, Alan |date=9 October 2015 |publisher=New York Times |archive-date=2020-12-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201209115853/https://www.nytimes.com/politics/first-draft/2015/09/10/bernie-sanders-has-a-fan-in-the-james-bond-actor-daniel-craig/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。1996年2月16日至17日對当时美国总统候选人[[帕特·布坎南|帕特·布坎南]]是白人至上主义的支持者的报道中，一位来自[[洛杉矶时报|洛杉矶时报]]以及[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]的记者发表评论，指其为一个支持自由主义的组织（liberal group）<ref name="LATimes">{{cite news|url=http://articles.latimes.com/print/1996-02-16/news/mn-36754_1_pat-buchanan|title=Buchanan Aide Suspended Over Hate Group Ties|last=Broder|first=John|date=1996-02-16|work=[[洛杉磯時報|洛杉磯時報]]|accessdate=2001-01-31|archive-date=2013-01-27|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130127230909/http://articles.latimes.com/print/1996-02-16/news/mn-36754_1_pat-buchanan|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="NYT">{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/1996/02/17/opinion/mr-buchanan-stumbles.html|title=Mr. Buchanan Stumbles|date=1996-02-17|work=[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]|accessdate=2001-01-31|archive-date=2020-09-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200904060649/https://www.nytimes.com/1996/02/17/opinion/mr-buchanan-stumbles.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

